1.author: filler
1.title: Quote of day 1
1.body: “I had been told that the training procedure with cats was difficult. It’s not. Mine had me trained in two days.” – Bill Dana

2.author: filler
2.title: Quote of day 2
2.body: “Cats are inquisitive, but hate to admit it.” – Mason Cooley

3.author: filler
3.title: Quote of day 3
3.body: “In ancient times cats were worshipped as gods; they have not forgotten this.” – Terry Pratchett

4.author: filler
4.title: Quote of day 4
4.body: “I have studied many philosophers and many cats. The wisdom of cats is infinitely superior.” – Hippolyte Taine

5.author: filler
5.title: Quote of day 5
5.body: “There are two means of refuge from the miseries of life: music and cats.” – Albert Schweitzer

6.author: filler
6.title: Quote of day 6
6.body: “A happy arrangement: many people prefer cats to other people, and many cats prefer people to other cats.” – Mason Cooley

7.author: filler
7.title: Quote of day 7
7.body: “How we behave toward cats here below determines our status in heaven.” – Robert A. Heinlein

8.author: filler
8.title: Quote of day 8
8.body: “You can not look at a sleeping cat and feel tense.” – Jane Pauley

9.author: filler
9.title: Quote of day 9
9.body: “I love my cats more than I love most people. Probably more than is healthy.” – Amy Lee

10.author: filler
10.title: Quote of day 10
10.body: “All you need is love and a cat.” – Unknown
